        - `String`Â (object): This is a wrapper object that JavaScript automatically wraps around the string primitive when you use properties or methods on a string (e.g.,Â `let str = new String('hello')`). It's generally recommended to use string primitives (`string`) instead of string objects (`String`) in JavaScript for performance reasons.

